-06T14:51:24Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/aceArt-GmbH/sdl2-bug\r\n\r\nwith `cargo run` and `cargo run --release`\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: assert should pass like it does on builds without lto (or dev builds)\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: after `set_viewport` the value changes in release build with lto. Disabling lto or removing the `set_viewport` call \"fixes\" the problem.\r\n\r\nAdding a `dbg!(&before);` to line 19 changes the values enormously.\r\n\r\nRef issue: https://github.com/Rust-SDL2/rust-sdl2/issues/1168\r\n\r\nI am not sure if this is a problem from rust-sdl2, sdl2, llvm or Rust. I would expect a Rust program to behave the same way in release builds (with lto) as in dev builds.\r\n(I also tried reproducing the example in C++ directly, but I did not mange to do it. Maybe because of lacking C++ knowledge)\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n<!--\r\nIf you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the\r\nbug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.59.0-nightly (e2116acae 2021-12-05)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: e2116acae59654bfab2a9729a024f3e2fd6d4b02\r\ncommit-date: 2021-12-05\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.59.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 13.0.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n```\r\nthread 'main' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)`\r\n  left: `Rect { x: 0, y: 0, w: 800, h: 600 }`,\r\n right: `Rect { x: 0, y: 800, w: 600, h: 5 }`', src/main.rs:22:5\r\n```\r\n\r\nor with a `dbg!(&before);` on line 19\r\n\r\n```\r\nthread 'main' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)`\r\n  left: `Rect { x: 0, y: 0, w: 800, h: 600 }`,\r\n right: `Rect { x: 22049, y: 492258464, w: 22049, h: 492398784 }`', src/main.rs:23:5\r\n```\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>", "closed_by": {"login": "fee1-dead", "id": 43851243, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcj